§22. In almost all the above passages the separated adjectives have a special significance3 but most of the examples in the C. S. seem to serve no purpose, and are merely a metrical convenience. This is perhaps true of many cases where the adjectives corne last.

§²3- It should be observed that in the examples cited at ἓ 21 the adjective and noun are construed with the verb. Five passages viz. Odcs 1. 5. 2, 1. 22. 11, 1. 26. 4, 3. 14. 21, and 4. 9. 49 are somewhat different. For these see the notes ad loc.
